Last abdominal ventrite (
Figs 43, 45
) enlarged, subtrapezoidal, median lobe with posterior margin straight, lateral parts of ventrite with large semicircular emarginations, surface of median lobe with chanelled impression slightly wider posteriorly. In lateral view, last abdominal ventrite distinctly concave in middle.

Aedeagus (
Fig. 26
) flat, with apical third triangular, middle part wide and subparallel. Dorsal surface with two long parallel carinae medially and two shorter oblique carinae laterally. In lateral view, aedeagus strongly curved in apical half.
